author: @DramaticBaby
text: For future reference: - In Bootstrap 4 the class "nav-stacked" must be replaced with "flex-column". - All <li> elements must have the class "nav-item" added to them. - All <a> elements must have the class "nav-link" added to them. See https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.0/components/navs/ for an explanation of the classes.

I received no errors but the styles did not apply.  I created an exact copy of the header page outside of the django framework (minus the Jinja logic) with an exact copy of the style sheet that i used in my "styles" dir and everything worked perfectly.  Today I have the same problem. I am not getting any errors ("stylesheet not found" etc) but the styles will no apply to the "header".  I checked StackOverflow for answers. The only thing I could find that worked for anyone was to go to "encoding" in Notepad++ and click "convert to UTF-8" then select "UTF-8" again. This did not work for me.  If you have any idea what this problem may be please let me know. I want to follow along but I am at a loss here ):
